<subSubSection id="C3776556EDD438B2FC9AF879FEBBFC14" lastPageId="647" lastPageNumber="648" pageId="645" pageNumber="646" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD438B2FC9AF879FE48FE38" blockId="645.[810,1452,1738,2070]" lastBlockId="647.[136,778,173,1492]" lastPageId="647" lastPageNumber="648" pageId="645" pageNumber="646">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD438B0FC9AF879FB9CF810" bold="true" box="[863,1113,1975,2001]" pageId="645" pageNumber="646">Descriptionoffemale</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD438B0FB6BF876FAE4F813" box="[1198,1313,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 439" captionStartId="646.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[249,1332,214,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-21@646.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="646" captionText="FIGURE 439. Haplostatus dakarensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, left, with inset showing claw–like process on anal somite; C, posterior end of body, dorsal; D, cephalic region, right; E, cephalic region, ventral; F, antennule, dorsal; G, antennule, ventral; H, antenna; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.05 mm; F–H, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592198/files/figure.png" pageId="645" pageNumber="646">Fig. 439A</figureCitation>
) vermiform, cylindrical, slightly arched ventrally, narrowing anteriorly and posteriorly, without any metameric subdivision. Body length 4.42 mm in 
<typeStatus id="54D6887FEDD638B2FEA2FF63FE08FF06" box="[359,461,173,199]" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">holotype</typeStatus>
; greatest width 1.12 mm in middle; body lengths of 
<specimenCount id="9D6BFD54EDD638B2FE61FF01FDE3FF28" box="[420,550,207,233]" pageId="647" pageNumber="648" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">2 paratypes</specimenCount>
3.04 and 5.20 mm. Body surface smooth, without ornamentation of setules or wrinkles. Freeurosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD638B2FE60FEDDFDF9FEEC" box="[421,572,275,301]" captionStart="FIGURE 439" captionStartId="646.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[249,1332,214,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-21@646.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="646" captionText="FIGURE 439. Haplostatus dakarensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, left, with inset showing claw–like process on anal somite; C, posterior end of body, dorsal; D, cephalic region, right; E, cephalic region, ventral; F, antennule, dorsal; G, antennule, ventral; H, antenna; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.05 mm; F–H, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592198/files/figure.png" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">Fig. 439B, C</figureCitation>
) short, occupying 7% of total body length, obscurely 3-segmented, with additional partial suture line (or wrinkle) dorsally, anterior to first urosomite and 4 faint sclerotization bands on dorsal side (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD638B2FF0FFE55FE81FE74" box="[202,324,411,437]" captionStart="FIGURE 439" captionStartId="646.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[249,1332,214,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-21@646.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="646" captionText="FIGURE 439. Haplostatus dakarensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, left, with inset showing claw–like process on anal somite; C, posterior end of body, dorsal; D, cephalic region, right; E, cephalic region, ventral; F, antennule, dorsal; G, antennule, ventral; H, antenna; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.05 mm; F–H, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592198/files/figure.png" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">Fig. 439C</figureCitation>
). Last urosomite (anal somite) weakly bilobed; each lobe tipped with small, pointed, claw-like process (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD638B2FF2EFE11FE45FE38" box="[235,384,479,505]" captionStart="FIGURE 439" captionStartId="646.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[249,1332,214,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-21@646.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="646" captionText="FIGURE 439. Haplostatus dakarensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, left, with inset showing claw–like process on anal somite; C, posterior end of body, dorsal; D, cephalic region, right; E, cephalic region, ventral; F, antennule, dorsal; G, antennule, ventral; H, antenna; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.05 mm; F–H, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592198/files/figure.png" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">Fig. 439B, C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF126655EDD738B3FF4DF8BDFDD3F835" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592198" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4592198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592198/files/figure.png" pageId="646" pageNumber="647" startId="646.[136,245,1907,1933]" targetBox="[249,1332,214,1837]" targetPageId="646">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD738B3FF4DF8BDFDD3F835" blockId="646.[136,1451,1907,2037]" pageId="646" pageNumber="647">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD738B3FF4DF8BDFEEAF84F" bold="true" box="[136,303,1907,1934]" pageId="646" pageNumber="647">FIGURE 439.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD738B3FEFDF8BAFD84F84F" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[312,577,1908,1934]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Haplostatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="646" pageNumber="647" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dakarensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD738B3FEFDF8BAFD84F84F" box="[312,577,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="646" pageNumber="647">Haplostatus dakarensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EDD738B3FD8FF8BAFD62F84F" box="[586,679,1908,1934]" pageId="646" pageNumber="647" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD738B3FD8FF8BAFD64F84F" bold="true" box="[586,673,1908,1934]" pageId="646" pageNumber="647">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, left, with inset showing claw–like process on anal somite; C, posterior end of body, dorsal; D, cephalic region, right; E, cephalic region, ventral; F, antennule, dorsal; G, antennule, ventral; H, antenna; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.05 mm; F–H, 0.02 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD638B2FF78FDCCFE67FCEA" blockId="647.[136,778,173,1492]" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD638B2FEEBFDCFFE06FDDD" box="[302,451,513,540]" captionStart="FIGURE 439" captionStartId="646.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[249,1332,214,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-21@646.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="646" captionText="FIGURE 439. Haplostatus dakarensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, left, with inset showing claw–like process on anal somite; C, posterior end of body, dorsal; D, cephalic region, right; E, cephalic region, ventral; F, antennule, dorsal; G, antennule, ventral; H, antenna; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.05 mm; F–H, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592198/files/figure.png" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">Fig. 439D, E</figureCitation>
) distinct, slightly widerthan long, tapering towards rounded distal margin. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD638B2FF55FD8BFEE8FD9E" box="[144,301,581,607]" captionStart="FIGURE 439" captionStartId="646.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[249,1332,214,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-21@646.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="646" captionText="FIGURE 439. Haplostatus dakarensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, left, with inset showing claw–like process on anal somite; C, posterior end of body, dorsal; D, cephalic region, right; E, cephalic region, ventral; F, antennule, dorsal; G, antennule, ventral; H, antenna; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.05 mm; F–H, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592198/files/figure.png" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">Fig. 439F, G</figureCitation>
) lobate, unsegmented, widerthan long, ornamented with few, minute spinules subdistally. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD638B2FF3DFD47FEABFD62" box="[248,366,649,675]" captionStart="FIGURE 439" captionStartId="646.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[249,1332,214,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-21@646.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="646" captionText="FIGURE 439. Haplostatus dakarensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, left, with inset showing claw–like process on anal somite; C, posterior end of body, dorsal; D, cephalic region, right; E, cephalic region, ventral; F, antennule, dorsal; G, antennule, ventral; H, antenna; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.05 mm; F–H, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592198/files/figure.png" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">Fig. 439H</figureCitation>
) located deep inside pre-oral cavity (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD638B2FF55FD65FEC2FD04" box="[144,263,683,709]" captionStart="FIGURE 439" captionStartId="646.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[249,1332,214,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-21@646.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="646" captionText="FIGURE 439. Haplostatus dakarensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, left, with inset showing claw–like process on anal somite; C, posterior end of body, dorsal; D, cephalic region, right; E, cephalic region, ventral; F, antennule, dorsal; G, antennule, ventral; H, antenna; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.05 mm; F–H, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592198/files/figure.png" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">Fig. 439D</figureCitation>
); stout, 2-segmented, both segments unarmed; distal (endopodal) segment strongly tapering, fused to terminal claw, leaving only partial non-sclerotized region as vestige of articulation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD638B2FF78FCFDFDF6FC72" blockId="647.[136,778,173,1492]" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">
Labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD638B2FEECFCFDFE50FC8C" box="[297,405,819,845]" captionStart="FIGURE 439" captionStartId="646.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[249,1332,214,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-21@646.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="646" captionText="FIGURE 439. Haplostatus dakarensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, left, with inset showing claw–like process on anal somite; C, posterior end of body, dorsal; D, cephalic region, right; E, cephalic region, ventral; F, antennule, dorsal; G, antennule, ventral; H, antenna; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.05 mm; F–H, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592198/files/figure.png" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">Fig. 439I</figureCitation>
) broadening posteriorly, located deep inside pre-oral cavity, unornamented, with slightly concave posterior margin. Mandibles, maxillules, maxillae, maxillipeds and legs absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD638B2FF78FC75FEBBFC14" blockId="647.[136,778,173,1492]" box="[189,382,955,982]" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD638B2FF78FC75FF3FFC14" bold="true" box="[189,250,955,981]" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556EDD638B2FF78FC13FD73FA15" pageId="647" pageNumber="648" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD638B2FF78FC13FD73FA15" blockId="647.[136,778,173,1492]" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD638B2FF78FC13FEEDFC36" bold="true" box="[189,296,989,1015]" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD638B2FEFEFC13FDFBFC36" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[315,574,989,1015]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Haplostatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="647" pageNumber="648" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incubatrix">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD638B2FEFEFC13FDFBFC36" box="[315,574,989,1015]" italics="true" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">Haplostatus incubatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus id="54D6887FEDD638B2FDBAFC10FD6BFC39" box="[639,686,990,1016]" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus, is associated with the compound ascidian 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD638B2FF4DFBEFFDB5FBFA" authority="(Della Valle, 1877)" baseAuthorityName="Della Valle" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[136,624,1057,1083]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Polycitoridae" genus="Cystodytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="647" pageNumber="648" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dellechiajei">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD638B2FF4DFBEFFE4FFBFA" box="[136,394,1057,1083]" italics="true" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">Cystodytes dellechiajei</emphasis>
(Della Valle, 1877)
</taxonomicName>
found in the Mediterranean Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CEDD638B2FEB1FB8DFDAEFB9F" author="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L." box="[372,619,1091,1118]" journalOrPublisher="Vie et Milieu, Supplement" pageId="647" pageNumber="648" pagination="1 - 126" part="12" refId="ref329073" refString="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L. (1961) Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer. Vie et Milieu, Supplement 12, 1 - 126." title="Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer" type="journal article" year="1961">
Illg &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="49A9F83FEDD638B2FE09FB8DFDDBFB9C" box="[460,542,1091,1117]" country="United Kingdom" name="Dudley" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">Dudley</collectingRegion>
, 1961
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD638B2FD40FB8DFF3BFBBE" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Haplostatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="647" pageNumber="648" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dakarensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD638B2FD40FB8DFF3BFBBE" italics="true" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">Haplostatus dakarensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD638B2FECAFBABFEB4FBBE" bold="true" box="[271,369,1125,1151]" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EDD638B2FECAFBABFEB4FBBE" box="[271,369,1125,1151]" pageId="647" pageNumber="648" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from 
<typeStatus id="54D6887FEDD638B2FDE5FBABFD44FB41" box="[544,641,1125,1152]" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">thetype</typeStatus>
species as follows: (1) the body surface is smooth, without setules or wrinkles, compared to the presence of an ornamentation of fine setules over the entire body surface in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD638B2FDAAFB02FCC6FB24" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[623,771,1227,1254]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Haplostatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="647" pageNumber="648" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incubatrix">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD638B2FDAAFB02FD46FB24" box="[623,643,1228,1253]" italics="true" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD638B2FD57FB05FCC6FB24" box="[658,771,1227,1253]" italics="true" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">incubatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CEDD638B2FEFFFB23FDEDFAC9" author="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L." box="[314,552,1261,1288]" journalOrPublisher="Vie et Milieu, Supplement" pageId="647" pageNumber="648" pagination="1 - 126" part="12" refId="ref329073" refString="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L. (1961) Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer. Vie et Milieu, Supplement 12, 1 - 126." title="Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer" type="journal article" year="1961">
Illg &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="49A9F83FEDD638B2FE41FB23FE10FAC6" box="[388,469,1261,1287]" country="United Kingdom" name="Dudley" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">Dudley</collectingRegion>
(1961)
</bibRefCitation>
; (2) the antennule is wider than long and carries a few spinules, compared to the antennule of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD638B2FEDCFAFCFE69FA8A" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[281,428,1329,1356]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Haplostatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="647" pageNumber="648" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incubatrix">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD638B2FEDCFAFCFEE8FA8A" box="[281,301,1330,1355]" italics="true" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD638B2FEFEFAFFFE69FA8A" box="[315,428,1329,1355]" italics="true" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">incubatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which is longer than wide (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CEDD638B2FD27FAFFFEFEFAAF" author="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L." journalOrPublisher="Vie et Milieu, Supplement" pageId="647" pageNumber="648" pagination="1 - 126" part="12" refId="ref329073" refString="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L. (1961) Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer. Vie et Milieu, Supplement 12, 1 - 126." title="Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer" type="journal article" year="1961">
Illg &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="49A9F83FEDD638B2FF61FA9DFF33FAAC" box="[164,246,1363,1389]" country="United Kingdom" name="Dudley" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">Dudley</collectingRegion>
, 1961
</bibRefCitation>
); (3) the endopod and terminal claw of the antenna are fused, compared to the free terminal claw of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD638B2FD2AFAB8FF3CFA70" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Haplostatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="647" pageNumber="648" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incubatrix">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD638B2FD2AFAB8FCC6FA4E" box="[751,771,1398,1423]" italics="true" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD638B2FF4DFA59FF3CFA70" box="[136,249,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">incubatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and (4) the mouthparts are all lacking, whereas one pair of mouthparts is retained in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD638B2FDD8FA74FD6AFA12" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[541,687,1465,1492]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Haplostatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="647" pageNumber="648" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incubatrix">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD638B2FDD8FA74FDF4FA12" box="[541,561,1466,1491]" italics="true" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD638B2FDFBFA77FD6AFA12" box="[574,687,1465,1491]" italics="true" pageId="647" pageNumber="648">incubatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
